00:17:55,741 --> 00:17:59,377
So, let's do that by making
the hands of the clock point at 00:00

521
00:17:59,612 --> 00:18:04,649
And the key to solving the rest of the code
Is what your father had left behind

523
00:18:04,650 --> 00:18:05,684
by writing in blood the final ace!

524
00:18:05,685 --> 00:18:07,819
This refers to playing cards in English!

525
00:18:08,521 --> 00:18:11,823
The King, Queen and Jack in the code

526
00:18:11,824 --> 00:18:15,627
are the King, Queen and Jack
of the playing cards!

528
00:18:15,628 --> 00:18:21,132
The treasure is diamond the chalice
is heart and the dagger is spade

530
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:25,203
In other words, the treasure and the King
the king of diamonds!

532
00:18:25,204 --> 00:18:28,406
The chalice and the Queen
the queen of hearts!

534
00:18:28,407 --> 00:18:31,476
The dagger and the wainnior
the jack of spades!

536
00:18:32,044 --> 00:18:34,445
First you bring the hands
of the clock to 00:00...

538
00:18:34,446 --> 00:18:36,982
then you move the hands of the clock
In accordance to the direction

540
00:18:36,983 --> 00:18:39,416
their faces are turned...

541
00:18:39,852 --> 00:18:41,453
Left 13,

542
00:18:41,554 --> 00:18:43,188
Left 12,

544
00:18:43,990 --> 00:18:46,491
Right 11, then...

546
00:18:46,492 --> 00:18:46,691
Right 11, then...

549
00:18:55,868 --> 00:18:57,569
The polish has rubbed off

550
00:18:57,570 --> 00:18:58,970
and gold is in view on the inside...

551
00:18:59,672 --> 00:19:02,474
Moreover, this clock
IS heavier than it looks...

553
00:19:02,475 --> 00:19:06,111
I see...the inside of this clock
IS pure gold

555
00:19:07,813 --> 00:19:12,250
to think that my father had to die
for something like that

557
00:19:12,251 --> 00:19:14,352
I guess that's life

558
00:19:15,554 --> 00:19:18,256
So, you promised, Ms. Senma

559
00:19:18,257 --> 00:19:20,925
Tell me the way out of this place!

560
00:19:21,292 --> 00:19:23,928
There is no way out of here to begin with

561
00:19:23,929 --> 00:19:26,698
I was planning to bury my bones here,
you see...

563
00:19:27,199 --> 00:19:30,702
Although Mr. Ogami did believe me
when I told him

565
00:19:30,703 --> 00:19:33,338
that I would tell him
the way after dinner...

567
00:19:33,672 --> 00:19:35,106
Just as I thought

568
00:19:35,107 --> 00:19:37,541
Granny Senma...

569
00:19:37,710 --> 00:19:40,310
What're you going to do about
the only valuable I had on me?

571
00:19:40,613 --> 00:19:44,949
Remember I told you that something
childish like this isn't worth it...

573
00:19:45,785 --> 00:19:48,053
Complain to sonny over there
If you got any gripes

575
00:19:48,721 --> 00:19:52,490
» He's the one who said that
she may tell us the way out

577
00:19:52,491 --> 00:19:53,791
if a child asked to know...

578
00:19:54,593 --> 00:19:58,329
You mean you all pretended to be dead
just so that I would tell you the way out?

580
00:19:59,732 --> 00:20:02,767
Because you were even trying to kill
the ones who figured the code out

582
00:20:03,369 --> 00:20:05,370
We figured that you wouldn't tell us

583
00:20:05,371 --> 00:20:07,906
even if we cornered
you so long as we were alive

585
00:20:08,273 --> 00:20:11,976
Besides, throu h the monitor
even ketchup looks like blood!

587
